# 🏢 Xcelerate Group – Identity Automation Platform  
## Enterprise Identity Lifecycle Automation (Active Directory + Microsoft 365)

---

# 🧠 Overview

Xcelerate Group required a modernised **Identity and Access Management (IAM) system** to replace a manual, inconsistent onboarding/offboarding process.

The solution implemented an **automated identity lifecycle platform** integrating:

- Microsoft Forms (Request Intake)
- Power Automate (Workflow Engine)
- Active Directory (Identity Source of Truth)
- Microsoft 365 (Email & Collaboration)
- Excel / SharePoint (Audit & Tracking)

---

# 🚨 1. Problem Statement

The organisation had a fully manual identity management process leading to:

- Manual onboarding/offboarding via email and spreadsheets  
- No central identity workflow system  
- Delayed account provisioning (24–72 hours)  
- No approval governance for identity requests  
- Inconsistent Active Directory user creation  
- No audit trail for identity changes  
- High IT workload due to repetitive tasks  
- No integration between Active Directory and Microsoft 365 lifecycle  

---

# ⚠️ Critical Security Issue Identified

A major security flaw was discovered:

> Standard users were incorrectly assigned the same access permissions as managers.

### Impact:
- Broken Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
- Over-privileged user accounts
- No separation of duties (SoD)
- Exposure of sensitive departmental data
- Violated least privilege security principle

---

# 🔐 Security Fix Implemented

### RBAC Model Redesign:
- Separated security groups:
  - Standard Users
  - Managers
  - Admins
  - Finance (Restricted)

### Enforcement:
- NTFS permissions corrected on shared drives
- AD security groups restructured
- Automated role assignment via onboarding workflow

### Outcome:
- Least privilege model enforced
- Reduced privilege escalation risk
- Improved compliance posture

---

# 🏢 2. Environment

- On-Prem Active Directory (Windows Server 2016/2019)
