# 🏗️ 3. Architecture Overview

The system follows a full **identity lifecycle automation model**:

- Forms → Request Intake  
- Power Automate → Validation & Approval  
- Active Directory → Identity Creation  
- Microsoft 365 → License & Mailbox Provisioning  
- GPO → Device & Security Enforcement  
- SharePoint/Excel → Audit Logging  

---

# ⚙️ 4. Implementation Process

## Step 1: User Request Intake
- Microsoft Forms used for onboarding/offboarding requests
- Required fields enforced (name, department, role)

---

## Step 2: Validation & Approval Flow
- Power Automate validates request completeness
- Manager approval required before processing

---

## Step 3: Identity Processing Engine
- Standardised usernames (firstname.lastname)
- Duplicate account detection
- Data cleanup before provisioning

---

## Step 4: Active Directory Provisioning
- Automated user creation in AD
- OU placement based on role:
  - Staff
  - IT
  - Contractors
  - Finance

---

## Step 5: Security Group Assignment (RBAC)
- Users assigned to correct security groups:
  - Standard Users
  - Managers
  - Admins

---

## Step 6: Microsoft 365 Integration
- Automatic:
  - Mailbox creation
  - Teams access
  - SharePoint permissions

---

## Step 7: Device & Policy Enforcement
- Domain join automation
- Group Policy applied:
  - Password policies
  - Desktop restrictions
  - Drive mappings

---

## Step 8: Audit & Tracking
- All actions logged into Excel / SharePoint
- Full identity lifecycle traceability

---

## Step 9: Offboarding Automation
- Disable AD account
- Revoke Microsoft 365 access
- Retain logs for compliance

---

